WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:08.747
- Previously
on "Briarpatch"...

00:08.791 --> 00:10.227
- I'm gonna see you next week
for the reunion?

00:10.271 --> 00:12.055
It's our 20th.
Ugh.

00:12.099 --> 00:13.578
- Raytek planted the story,

00:13.622 --> 00:14.797
threw my sister under the bus,

00:14.840 --> 00:16.146
and then drove that bus
right over her

00:16.190 --> 00:17.800
on her way to city hall.
I wanna know why.

00:17.843 --> 00:19.367
- You ever think
there was a reason

00:19.410 --> 00:20.672
why Felicity
never ask you for help?

00:20.716 --> 00:21.717
- Fuck you.

00:21.760 --> 00:23.327
- The only reason I'm spending

00:23.371 --> 00:25.851
more than a heartbeat here
is to ruin someone's life.

00:25.895 --> 00:27.679
Jake has done
some terrible things.

00:27.723 --> 00:28.854
[gunshot]

00:28.898 --> 00:31.161
Terrible, awful,
shocking things.

00:31.205 --> 00:33.468
- [grunting]

00:33.511 --> 00:35.078
- And I can prove them all.

00:35.122 --> 00:36.688
- The Senator wants a sit-down
with Clyde Brattle.

00:36.732 --> 00:38.212
- You can't be serious.

00:38.255 --> 00:40.127
- If you think there's value
in me meeting with Spivey,

00:40.170 --> 00:41.171
then I will.

00:41.215 --> 00:42.477
- I'll set it up for tomorrow.

00:42.520 --> 00:44.174
- I heard you got your meeting
for Jake Spivey.

00:44.218 --> 00:46.307
This was the first time
you disobeyed me.

00:46.350 --> 00:47.743
It is also the last.

00:47.786 --> 00:50.702
I will not hesitate
to put you back in.

00:50.746 --> 00:52.313
Permanently.

00:52.356 --> 00:53.879
- The Senator, he's a good man.
He'll listen.

00:53.923 --> 00:55.881
You'll tell him everything?
About Al-Namur?

00:55.925 --> 00:58.145
It's just us now,
and I need you to win.

00:58.188 --> 01:01.061
One meeting, we both get free.

01:03.280 --> 01:06.196
[Dolly Parton's
"Bubbling Over"]

01:06.240 --> 01:08.198
[cheery country music]

01:08.242 --> 01:10.374
[water bubbling]

01:10.418 --> 01:13.899
♪

01:13.943 --> 01:16.250
- ♪ You're the one
that puts the sparkle ♪

01:16.293 --> 01:18.643
♪ In my eyes

01:18.687 --> 01:20.776
♪ And you're the one
that puts the laughter ♪

01:20.819 --> 01:23.344
♪ In my smile

01:23.387 --> 01:25.389
♪ You're the one
that puts the meaning ♪

01:25.433 --> 01:27.391
♪ In my life

01:27.435 --> 01:30.568
[dog barking]
♪ And I'm bubbling over

01:30.612 --> 01:32.831
♪ Bubbling over

01:32.875 --> 01:34.355
♪ Bubbling over

01:34.398 --> 01:37.923
♪ Because you are mine

01:37.967 --> 01:40.274
[buzzing]
♪ Bubbling over with the joy

01:40.317 --> 01:42.450
♪ That only love can bring

01:42.493 --> 01:44.756
♪ Bubbling over
with the song ♪

01:44.800 --> 01:47.933
♪ You taught my heart
to sing ♪

01:47.977 --> 01:50.762
♪ Oh, and I'm so happy
loving you ♪

01:50.806 --> 01:53.722
♪ Anyone can see
that I'm ♪

01:53.765 --> 01:55.854
♪ Bubbling over
[buzzing]

01:55.898 --> 01:57.900
♪ Bubbling over
[music fades]

01:58.814 --> 02:00.511
[buzzing]

02:00.555 --> 02:02.296
[buzz]
- Ow!

02:02.339 --> 02:05.386
[buzzing continues]

02:11.740 --> 02:15.744
[louder buzzing]

02:17.963 --> 02:21.445
- ♪ Want to share
my loving with ♪

02:21.489 --> 02:23.665
♪ Your gentle way
of loving me ♪

02:23.708 --> 02:25.754
♪ And your thoughtfulness

02:25.797 --> 02:28.931
♪ Keeps me bubbling over

02:28.974 --> 02:31.586
♪ Bubbling over

02:31.629 --> 02:33.196
♪ Bubbling over

02:33.240 --> 02:35.633
♪ With happiness

02:35.677 --> 02:39.246
[funky music]

02:39.289 --> 02:41.770
- Police have identified
Lucretia Colder

02:41.813 --> 02:44.294
of the Heights district
as the sole suspect

02:44.338 --> 02:45.730
in last night's
fatal shooting.

02:45.774 --> 02:47.254
Colder, the wife

02:47.297 --> 02:49.299
of homicide captain
Eugene Colder,

02:49.343 --> 02:50.822
has been placed
on psychiatric hold

02:50.866 --> 02:52.172
and is awaiting arraignment.

02:52.215 --> 02:55.740
The victim, one Harold Snow
of Texas Avenue,

02:55.784 --> 02:58.003
has been described
as a "spirited creep"

02:58.047 --> 02:59.483
by neighbors.

02:59.527 --> 03:00.441
Speaking of spirit--

03:00.484 --> 03:02.225
- Can we have a do-over?

03:02.269 --> 03:03.922
- Longhorn patriotism
was on full display last night

03:03.966 --> 03:07.361
as Senator Joseph Ramirez
made his case for reelection--

03:07.404 --> 03:08.884
- I want people
to stop dying.

03:08.927 --> 03:10.842
- I'm Ginger Galanti,
and that is all--

03:10.886 --> 03:13.236
- You do realize that'd put me
out of business, right?

03:13.280 --> 03:19.764
♪

03:20.896 --> 03:22.506
Your world is rough.

03:22.550 --> 03:28.425
♪

03:28.469 --> 03:31.907
- Lucretia Colder doesn't have
an alibi.

03:31.950 --> 03:33.343
For either of the bombs.

03:33.387 --> 03:34.953
- Lucretia Colder
can't make a soufflé,

03:34.997 --> 03:36.868
let alone a explosive device.

03:36.912 --> 03:39.001
Come on.
- If not her, then who?

03:39.044 --> 03:41.873
Raytek was out of town
for the first one.

03:41.917 --> 03:45.442
Colder...

03:45.486 --> 03:47.401
I mean, he says
he loved Felicity.

03:47.444 --> 03:50.273
- But did she love him back?

03:50.317 --> 03:52.928
- It's never made sense to me.

03:52.971 --> 03:55.409
But he couldn't have planted
the second one.

03:55.452 --> 03:57.846
He was at the station
that night.

03:57.889 --> 04:01.328
- You know, sometimes
the best way to find something

04:01.371 --> 04:03.504
is to stop looking so hard.

04:03.547 --> 04:05.462
You just gotta sit
with what's happening.

04:05.506 --> 04:09.553
Stop rushin'.

04:09.597 --> 04:12.991
- Maybe I'd understand you
better if...

04:13.035 --> 04:14.558
you said it in French.

04:14.602 --> 04:18.388
♪

04:18.432 --> 04:19.476
Fine.

04:19.520 --> 04:22.305
But I still have a job to do.

04:22.349 --> 04:25.090
The Senator has two meetings.

04:25.134 --> 04:27.745
And I have everything riding
on the first one at Jake's.

04:27.789 --> 04:29.573
- What about the other one?

04:29.617 --> 04:31.575
- Well, the Senator is meeting
with a homicidal monster,

04:31.619 --> 04:33.098
so it has to be
someplace secret.

04:33.142 --> 04:39.453
♪

04:39.496 --> 04:40.976
- That's secret,
all right.

04:41.019 --> 04:42.804
Is it set?

04:45.894 --> 04:47.939
- It's about to be.

04:47.983 --> 04:50.899
[dramatic music]

04:50.942 --> 04:56.600
♪

04:56.644 --> 04:57.949
- You changed your hotel lock.

04:57.993 --> 04:59.560
- You murdered my friend.

04:59.603 --> 05:01.083
- The boss wants
what he wants.

05:01.126 --> 05:02.606
And what he wants now
is a meeting

05:02.650 --> 05:05.696
with your candy-ass senator.

05:05.740 --> 05:07.045
- Tomorrow, 11:00 a.m.

05:07.089 --> 05:08.786
Here.

05:10.701 --> 05:12.616
- It was Harley, by the way.

05:12.660 --> 05:15.358
♪

05:15.402 --> 05:17.795
I prefer to work with my hands.

05:19.057 --> 05:20.755
Come on.

05:20.798 --> 05:22.626
I like it when you flinch.

05:22.670 --> 05:28.806
♪

05:28.850 --> 05:30.634
- Hey.
[laughs]

05:30.678 --> 05:32.375
Oh, I know
what you're thinking,

05:32.419 --> 05:34.725
but they use almond flour now,
you know.

05:34.769 --> 05:36.901
Besides,
Duke also needed a treat.

05:36.945 --> 05:38.990
'Cause the clinic laid him off.

05:39.034 --> 05:41.602
Apparently, it's mandatory
to wear gloves now.

05:41.645 --> 05:43.168
Oh, what a world.
Oh, what a world.

05:43.212 --> 05:45.083
- Excuse me, Barbara Jean.
- Whoo, look who's in a hurry!

05:45.127 --> 05:46.476
Listen, I just wanna tell you

05:46.520 --> 05:48.478
that I did reserve
two tickets for you

05:48.522 --> 05:49.784
even though
you weren't really good

05:49.827 --> 05:51.699
about getting your RSVP back.

05:51.742 --> 05:54.136
Répondez vous, s'il vous plaît.
Right?

05:54.179 --> 05:55.616
The reunion.

05:55.659 --> 05:57.400
It's tonight.

05:57.444 --> 05:58.706
Yeah.
Oh, come on.

05:58.749 --> 06:00.534
I know you've already
picked out a dress.

06:00.577 --> 06:02.840
Little black number, I bet,
huh?

06:02.884 --> 06:04.842
Yeah, something transitional.

06:04.886 --> 06:07.889
Funeral to fiesta,
no problem, huh?

06:07.932 --> 06:10.413
- Die in a fire, Barbara Jean.

06:10.457 --> 06:13.851
- [laughing] Oh, my God.

06:13.895 --> 06:15.026
Okay.

06:15.070 --> 06:17.202
She's not getting the discount.

06:17.246 --> 06:24.122
♪

06:28.126 --> 06:30.868
- Outside?

06:30.912 --> 06:32.217
- It's where Spivey wanted
to meet.

06:32.261 --> 06:34.002
- Come on, Cyrus.
[inhales deeply]

06:34.045 --> 06:35.699
Smell the air.

06:35.743 --> 06:37.788
These are Western
Soapberry trees.

06:37.832 --> 06:39.747
This is Texas.

06:39.790 --> 06:41.923
This is where I'm from.

06:41.966 --> 06:43.925
- [laughing] Hey!

06:45.796 --> 06:47.885
Welcome, gentlemen.
How are you?

06:47.929 --> 06:49.539
Nice to see you.

06:49.583 --> 06:51.019
Now, I know the man

06:51.062 --> 06:52.890
with a taste
for that native dendrology

06:52.934 --> 06:55.632
must be that famous
Senator Ramirez.

06:55.676 --> 06:58.026
Pleasure.
- You must be Mr. Spivey.

06:58.069 --> 07:00.202
- Oh, no.
Mr. Spivey was my daddy.

07:00.245 --> 07:01.725
And he died in an industrial
meat grinder.

07:01.769 --> 07:03.074
No, I'm Jake.

07:03.118 --> 07:05.033
Now, Senator, I put aside
a set of whites for you

07:05.076 --> 07:06.687
in the clubhouse
along with some shoes.

07:06.730 --> 07:08.210
Now, it's 12 wide, right?

07:08.253 --> 07:10.908
- That's right.
- All right.

07:10.952 --> 07:12.954
- Spivey appears
to have planned ahead.

07:12.997 --> 07:17.001
♪

07:18.960 --> 07:21.919
- [grunts]

07:21.963 --> 07:24.095
- Oh, not bad.

07:24.139 --> 07:26.489
- Well, I did play
on the croquet team at Exeter.

07:26.533 --> 07:28.709
- Oh.

07:30.145 --> 07:33.061
All right, so tell me,

07:33.104 --> 07:35.716
what is it that you're after?

07:35.759 --> 07:37.587
- A lot of American money
went missing

07:37.631 --> 07:39.502
in the Middle East.
- Ah!

07:39.546 --> 07:40.677
- My constituents
deserve to know

07:40.721 --> 07:42.287
where their tax dollars
went.

07:42.331 --> 07:44.681
- Money gets misspent
all the time.

07:44.725 --> 07:45.639
You know what I'm saying?

07:45.682 --> 07:47.205
Hey, one time,

07:47.249 --> 07:49.033
I paid 10 grand
for a leopard coat

07:49.077 --> 07:50.513
only to find out

07:50.557 --> 07:52.167
it was actually
a tiny coat for a leopard.

07:52.210 --> 07:54.517
Oh, heck.

07:54.561 --> 07:56.171
What do you say,
you want a beer?

07:57.781 --> 07:59.957
- I'd love one.

08:00.001 --> 08:02.003
♪

08:02.046 --> 08:04.092
- [crunching]

08:06.660 --> 08:08.096
The tamale spot.

08:08.139 --> 08:10.620
- There's a small apartment
in the back upstairs.

08:10.664 --> 08:13.318
11:00 a.m. tomorrow.
Brattle is confirmed.

08:13.362 --> 08:16.191
- Good to see you
back on the ball, Allegra Dill.

08:17.322 --> 08:19.977
Hmm.

08:20.021 --> 08:22.153
- Well, Allegra tells me
you're a real good guy.

08:22.197 --> 08:23.546
- [laughs]

08:23.590 --> 08:25.809
- But between us now,

08:25.853 --> 08:28.638
this here ain't politics.

08:28.682 --> 08:29.813
- Mm.

08:29.857 --> 08:31.554
- It's marketin'!

08:31.598 --> 08:32.816
And now look, Clyde,

08:32.860 --> 08:34.252
he can give you a whole bunch
of receipts

08:34.296 --> 08:36.080
that'll be sure to get
the Wall Street types

08:36.124 --> 08:39.301
all hot and bothered, but...

08:39.344 --> 08:41.825
I can give you something

08:41.869 --> 08:45.263
that'll get Joe Popcorn
crying in his cornflakes.

08:47.048 --> 08:51.792
You ever hear of Al-Namur?

08:51.835 --> 08:54.098
- Should I have?

08:54.142 --> 08:56.144
[bird cries]

08:56.187 --> 08:59.016
[tense music]

08:59.060 --> 09:01.845
- Back in 2012,

09:01.889 --> 09:05.283
our outfit was contracted
to arm rebels

09:05.327 --> 09:07.155
in and around Aleppo.

09:07.198 --> 09:10.201
- We weren't officially
in Syria in 2012.

09:10.245 --> 09:11.333
- Yeah.
Oh, yeah.

09:11.376 --> 09:13.770
I wasn't officially
in Julie Congdon

09:13.814 --> 09:15.119
back in tenth grade either,

09:15.163 --> 09:16.904
but that didn't stop me
from telling everyone

09:16.947 --> 09:20.081
I wasn't no virgin no more.

09:20.124 --> 09:22.736
Anyhoo, this is
the sort of thing we'd done

09:22.779 --> 09:24.041
a thousand times previous.

09:24.085 --> 09:25.260
You get in, you get out,

09:25.303 --> 09:27.697
you preserve government
deniability

09:27.741 --> 09:29.394
and maybe, you know,

09:29.438 --> 09:31.701
skim a little bit
off the top for our troubles.

09:31.745 --> 09:32.963
And you should've seen
these rebels.

09:33.007 --> 09:34.225
Boy, I'm telling you,
they're just a bunch

09:34.269 --> 09:35.923
of Chechen dirtbags

09:35.966 --> 09:40.405
slamming shit vodka and...

09:40.449 --> 09:42.886
watching VHS tapes
of bum fights till dawn.

09:42.930 --> 09:44.758
- I don't see how this helps--

09:44.801 --> 09:47.151
- One night,
right before Aleppo fell,

09:47.195 --> 09:50.024
I get word that these rebels

09:50.067 --> 09:53.810
are actually secret jihadis

09:53.854 --> 09:56.813
planning on turning our weapons
against our allies.

09:56.857 --> 10:01.252
Only had a few hours to try
and get the weapons back.

10:01.296 --> 10:03.124
It took all night.

10:03.167 --> 10:07.824
♪

10:07.868 --> 10:11.915
I remember the guy
with the VHS tapes

10:11.959 --> 10:15.136
had a mole right here on...

10:15.179 --> 10:16.920
♪

10:16.964 --> 10:18.966
[muffled gunfire]

10:19.009 --> 10:22.099
Right here
on the back of his head.

10:22.143 --> 10:23.927
I stared at it when I--

10:25.973 --> 10:28.062
- When you what?

10:28.105 --> 10:31.021
- Look, what matters is

10:31.065 --> 10:33.067
they weren't jihadis, Senator.

10:33.110 --> 10:35.025
It was all a setup.

10:35.069 --> 10:38.768
All so a guy like Clyde,
who's already rich,

10:38.812 --> 10:41.379
could just get
a little bit richer.

10:41.423 --> 10:42.946
You understand?

10:42.990 --> 10:46.733
This here is a story.

10:46.776 --> 10:48.735
One that people need to hear.

10:48.778 --> 10:51.259
And one that people
can understand.

10:51.302 --> 10:54.001
So you give me immunity

10:54.044 --> 10:55.872
and a Bible to put my hand on,

10:55.916 --> 10:59.267
and I swear to Sam Houston

10:59.310 --> 11:01.791
you're White House bound.

11:01.835 --> 11:06.970
♪

11:07.014 --> 11:09.973
- He's chatty.

11:10.017 --> 11:12.193
Your friend.

11:12.236 --> 11:13.977
- Always has been.

11:14.021 --> 11:16.327
- Not sure the game
is going his way.

11:16.371 --> 11:19.983
♪

11:20.027 --> 11:23.204
- Cyrus mentioned something
to me about...

11:23.247 --> 11:26.076
♪

11:26.120 --> 11:29.427
About mass graves?

11:29.471 --> 11:32.169
- Well, I'm not proud

11:32.213 --> 11:35.520
of what I did that day.

11:35.564 --> 11:38.828
But Clyde's the one
we should be focusing on.

11:38.872 --> 11:42.092
- So it was Brattle
who did the killing.

11:42.136 --> 11:44.791
- Brattle never did anything
directly.

11:44.834 --> 11:46.357
- Well, what do you mean
"directly"?

11:46.401 --> 11:48.490
- Men like Clyde don't pull
the trigger themselves.

11:48.533 --> 11:50.361
- They just give the orders?

11:50.405 --> 11:52.015
- Yeah.
Well--

11:52.059 --> 11:54.365
- Well, what?
Hmm?

11:54.409 --> 11:56.890
- I mean, he messes with you,
you know?

11:56.933 --> 11:58.848
He makes you understand
what he wants

11:58.892 --> 12:01.155
before he actually
has to say it.

12:01.198 --> 12:02.983
But Joe, hey, you know,
here's the thing--

12:03.026 --> 12:05.420
- Mr. Spivey,
correct me if I'm wrong

12:05.463 --> 12:06.856
but it sounds to me

12:06.900 --> 12:08.249
like you just confessed
to a massacre.

12:08.292 --> 12:09.772
- What?
No!

12:09.816 --> 12:12.775
- Women, children...
- No.

12:12.819 --> 12:16.213
I don't know anything
about the women and kids, okay?

12:16.257 --> 12:18.563
Now look, I only did what I--

12:18.607 --> 12:22.132
[muffled gunfire]

12:22.176 --> 12:24.047
[groans]
Oh, Christ.

12:24.091 --> 12:25.222
All right, hey, look,

12:25.266 --> 12:27.921
you want something
a little less messy?

12:27.964 --> 12:29.792
Yemen.

12:29.836 --> 12:31.446
I mean,
there is a whole bunch of shit

12:31.489 --> 12:33.535
that went down in Yemen
that nobody knows about.

12:33.578 --> 12:37.452
Yeah, I'd say probably 2...

12:37.495 --> 12:40.063
and I'm a little bit fuzzy
on the year, but...

12:40.107 --> 12:43.806
♪

12:43.850 --> 12:45.895
- Let's go.

12:46.635 --> 12:48.506
- [grunts]
- Jesus Christ, Allegra.

12:48.550 --> 12:50.508
I can't put that guy
on television.

12:50.552 --> 12:53.947
Voters--they want a tax break,
not a horror story.

12:53.990 --> 12:56.079
- Give us a chance to--
- Us?

12:56.123 --> 12:58.255
What is "us"?

12:58.299 --> 13:00.083
We are the ones you work for,
Allegra,

13:00.127 --> 13:02.085
and we will see you tomorrow
morning for the Brattle meeting

13:02.129 --> 13:03.434
and that is the end of it.

13:07.961 --> 13:09.440
- Senator--
- You did good, kid.

13:09.484 --> 13:11.268
I can see why you like him.

13:11.312 --> 13:12.835
Let's wrap this up.

13:12.879 --> 13:16.491
I miss D.C.

13:16.534 --> 13:18.449
[engine turns over]

13:30.287 --> 13:33.203
[funky music]

13:33.247 --> 13:37.599
♪

13:37.642 --> 13:39.035
[knocks]

13:39.079 --> 13:41.168
- Gene.

13:42.560 --> 13:44.562
Are you living in here?

13:44.606 --> 13:46.913
- I can't go home.

13:46.956 --> 13:48.828
My house is a crime scene.

13:50.438 --> 13:52.483
An emotional crime scene.

13:52.527 --> 13:54.616
- Gene, can I give you
some advice?

13:54.659 --> 13:57.314
- I tried drinking diet.
I just don't like the taste.

13:57.358 --> 13:58.925
- Your fiancée's dead,

13:58.968 --> 14:00.491
your mentor blew up
two days later,

14:00.535 --> 14:02.276
and now your wife
is up at County

14:02.319 --> 14:04.669
waiting to be arraigned
on capital murder.

14:04.713 --> 14:07.368
The last place you oughta be
is at work.

14:07.411 --> 14:08.978
- I need my job.

14:09.022 --> 14:11.894
- You need sleep.

14:11.938 --> 14:14.027
Can't investigate this, Gene.
You're too close.

14:14.070 --> 14:16.159
To all of it.

14:16.203 --> 14:18.335
Look,
I could put you on leave,

14:18.379 --> 14:21.991
but I'm just gonna
put you to bed.

14:22.035 --> 14:23.471
Go on and hit the bunks, baby.

14:23.514 --> 14:25.125
Get a little sleep.

14:25.168 --> 14:28.955
♪

14:28.998 --> 14:30.130
- Thank you.

14:30.173 --> 14:33.524
♪

14:33.568 --> 14:35.135
- Go on.

14:35.178 --> 14:38.007
I'll get Mock to check on you
in a couple hours.

14:38.051 --> 14:40.575
Another Goddamn mess.

14:40.618 --> 14:41.706
I mean--

14:41.750 --> 14:44.013
- Damn it!
God damn it!

14:44.057 --> 14:45.667
[muttering]

14:45.710 --> 14:47.625
[grunts]

14:47.669 --> 14:48.670
- That won't help.

14:48.713 --> 14:51.499
- [grunting]

14:51.542 --> 14:54.067
[breathing heavily]

14:54.110 --> 14:57.331
That slick son of a bitch
set me up.

14:57.374 --> 14:59.507
And for what,
so I could take the fall

14:59.550 --> 15:03.076
for Clyde fucking Brattle?

15:03.119 --> 15:05.034
[gasps]
God damn it.

15:05.078 --> 15:07.645
- What now?

15:07.689 --> 15:10.170
- I got shot, remember?

15:10.213 --> 15:12.520
- You're not the only one
who got screwed here.

15:16.437 --> 15:19.309
Cyrus owns me.

15:19.353 --> 15:22.312
He's the one who got me
out of jail 12 years ago.

15:22.356 --> 15:24.749
I make one wrong move,

15:24.793 --> 15:26.664
I go back in.

15:29.102 --> 15:30.668
- Well, shit.

15:30.712 --> 15:34.716
- I won't let them
choose Brattle.

15:34.759 --> 15:37.588
Not after what he did to Lalo.

15:37.632 --> 15:39.373
And to you.

15:39.416 --> 15:42.593
Even if this ruins me.

15:42.637 --> 15:44.726
I can't.

15:44.769 --> 15:47.598
Maybe we'll have cells
near each other.

15:47.642 --> 15:51.080
- Ha. How is it I get rich
and you get fancy

15:51.124 --> 15:54.257
and 20 years later,
we're still here...

15:54.301 --> 15:57.086
getting fucked
by these blue bloods

15:57.130 --> 15:59.523
who only take the silver spoons
out their mouths

15:59.567 --> 16:03.092
just long enough to gobble up
our whole Goddamn lives?

16:03.136 --> 16:04.441
No.

16:04.485 --> 16:06.487
You know what?
It's our turn.

16:08.445 --> 16:09.577
Let's finish this.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.231
- Don't joke.

16:11.274 --> 16:13.233
- No, there ain't nothing funny
about what I'm proposing.

16:13.276 --> 16:16.323
I'm saying you and I
are gonna catch Clyde Brattle.

16:16.366 --> 16:18.194
Tonight.

16:18.238 --> 16:19.239
What?

16:19.282 --> 16:20.805
He's in town.

16:20.849 --> 16:22.633
You said it yourself
he likes to mess with me,

16:22.677 --> 16:25.332
so let's mess right back.

16:25.375 --> 16:29.466
Whoever controls Clyde...

16:29.510 --> 16:32.165
they control
the whole situation.

16:32.208 --> 16:35.298
- You, me, and what army?

16:35.342 --> 16:37.300
- Well, let me make a call.

16:37.344 --> 16:39.128
[doorbell chimes]

16:41.435 --> 16:43.785
- About time you
brung her up to speed.

16:43.828 --> 16:45.700
- [scoffs]

16:48.746 --> 16:50.748
Oh, she'll warm up.

17:08.810 --> 17:11.073
I'm sorry about that article.

17:11.117 --> 17:15.077
That case was messy.

17:15.121 --> 17:16.861
And it needed tidying.

17:16.905 --> 17:20.474
- [scoffs]

17:20.517 --> 17:23.868
- Look, I came to this town
'cause I wanted a challenge,

17:23.912 --> 17:27.655
but even I was thrown
by the venality on display.

17:27.698 --> 17:29.744
I mean, the mayor is a clown,

17:29.787 --> 17:32.268
he works for vampires,
and that dope in there

17:32.312 --> 17:34.314
sucking down beers
like a sump pump,

17:34.357 --> 17:36.316
well, him I could work with.
- I bet.

17:36.359 --> 17:38.144
- He really wants
to change things,

17:38.187 --> 17:39.667
and so do I.

17:39.710 --> 17:43.105
So a couple years back,
we hatched ourselves a plan.

17:43.149 --> 17:45.455
He'd buy up as much
of Packingtown as he could.

17:45.499 --> 17:48.719
I'd run for mayor.
Grant him the zoning rights

17:48.763 --> 17:50.765
to make something worthwhile
out of it all.

17:50.808 --> 17:54.116
- He can't develop anything.

17:54.160 --> 17:57.206
Not unless he gets immunity.

17:57.250 --> 18:01.428
- So we added
a few beats to the plan.

18:01.471 --> 18:03.343
I'd help him get Brattle,

18:03.386 --> 18:06.128
speed things along for when
people like you showed up.

18:06.172 --> 18:08.348
- Catching Brattle would make
an awfully good headline.

18:08.391 --> 18:11.525
- For what I hear,
it'd be good for the world.

18:11.568 --> 18:13.353
- And Felicity?

18:13.396 --> 18:16.356
[solemn music]

18:16.399 --> 18:18.140
♪

18:18.184 --> 18:20.534
- Your sister
was precious to me.

18:20.577 --> 18:23.189
Her death is on my conscience.

18:24.799 --> 18:28.455
But it's not on my hands.

18:28.498 --> 18:30.283
You help us collar Brattle
tonight,

18:30.326 --> 18:31.588
I'll make sure the world knows

18:31.632 --> 18:33.764
what kind of cop
your sister really was.

18:33.808 --> 18:39.248
♪

18:39.292 --> 18:41.468
You're angry, huh?

18:41.511 --> 18:43.513
Yeah, I used to be like you.

18:43.557 --> 18:45.907
The thing about anger is
it gives your power over

18:45.950 --> 18:48.257
to the person you're angry at.

18:48.301 --> 18:50.825
So I don't get angry anymore.
I get results.

18:50.868 --> 18:52.957
- You know
I'll never trust you.

18:53.001 --> 18:55.830
- Honey, I don't even know
if I like you.

18:55.873 --> 18:58.746
But that don't mean
we gals can't get shit done.

18:58.789 --> 19:03.794
♪

19:03.838 --> 19:06.623
If your senator's meeting
with Brattle tomorrow morning,

19:06.667 --> 19:08.973
then this has to happen
tonight.

19:09.017 --> 19:10.453
- Agreed.

19:12.803 --> 19:14.457
The only problem is

19:14.501 --> 19:16.285
no one can get in touch
with Brattle directly.

19:16.329 --> 19:20.811
♪

19:20.855 --> 19:22.900
What?

19:22.944 --> 19:24.641
- Tell her.

19:24.685 --> 19:31.213
♪

19:31.257 --> 19:33.172
- [grunts]

19:36.349 --> 19:39.700
[hair dryer whirring]

19:39.743 --> 19:42.703
[funky music]

19:42.746 --> 19:49.710
♪

19:53.496 --> 19:55.368
- You've had this
the whole time.

19:55.411 --> 19:57.848
- I try not to think about it.

19:57.892 --> 20:00.808
It ain't healthy, me and Clyde.

20:00.851 --> 20:02.549
Not a lot of guys
get away from him

20:02.592 --> 20:04.855
and that's 'cause most of 'em
don't really wanna leave.

20:04.899 --> 20:07.858
- You sure you're up to this?

20:07.902 --> 20:09.251
All right, well, good.

20:09.295 --> 20:10.513
He's got two goons left,

20:10.557 --> 20:12.472
so I can bring in
a man I trust.

20:12.515 --> 20:13.690
Our four to his three,

20:13.734 --> 20:15.605
but I'm still gonna need you
as the bait.

20:15.649 --> 20:16.693
- I'll be in your ear.

20:16.737 --> 20:18.347
- Never left, darling.

20:18.391 --> 20:20.697
- All that's left to decide
is where.

20:20.741 --> 20:22.569
- Well,
it's gonna have to be public.

20:22.612 --> 20:24.353
Otherwise, he won't show.
- Agreed.

20:24.397 --> 20:26.355
Somewhere cops don't look
out of place.

20:26.399 --> 20:29.489
- Clyde likes spectacle,
so we can't forget that.

20:29.532 --> 20:32.753
So it's gonna have to be
a party or...

20:32.796 --> 20:35.016
♪

20:35.059 --> 20:36.365
[scoffs]

20:36.409 --> 20:39.542
♪

20:39.586 --> 20:41.327
- No.
- Oh, yes!

20:41.370 --> 20:42.806
- No.

20:42.850 --> 20:45.331
No!
- It's too perfect.

20:45.374 --> 20:47.071
- What?

20:47.115 --> 20:51.293
♪

20:51.337 --> 20:52.729
- [sighs]

20:52.773 --> 20:54.688
I should've shot you myself.

20:54.731 --> 20:58.344
♪

20:58.387 --> 21:01.956
I hate you.
- [laughs]

21:03.958 --> 21:08.354
[muffled pop music]

21:08.397 --> 21:09.920
- And you're sure he's coming?

21:09.964 --> 21:12.967
- To the science room.
That's what the message said.

21:14.621 --> 21:17.580
And I bet you 200 bucks

21:17.624 --> 21:20.801
that Robbie Deck got fat.

21:20.844 --> 21:24.021
"Most likely to succeed,"
my ass.

21:26.372 --> 21:28.765
Well, how about some drinks?

21:28.809 --> 21:31.420
- How about a cyanide pill?

21:31.464 --> 21:36.686
♪

21:36.730 --> 21:38.949
[laughter, chatter]

21:38.993 --> 21:43.693
♪

21:43.737 --> 21:45.956
[phone buzzes]

21:46.000 --> 21:47.741
- Hey.
What's up?

21:47.784 --> 21:49.046
- You know,
something's been bugging me

21:49.090 --> 21:50.787
about the two bombs,

21:50.831 --> 21:53.529
so I'm doing some digging.

21:53.573 --> 21:55.792
Maybe you're rubbing off
on me.

21:55.836 --> 21:57.403
- Sounds messy.

21:57.446 --> 21:59.361
- Is that dance pop?
Where you at?

21:59.405 --> 22:01.363
- I'm at my...

22:01.407 --> 22:03.626
20th high school reunion.

22:03.670 --> 22:06.020
- Socializin'.

22:06.063 --> 22:07.630
Who's rubbing off on who?

22:07.674 --> 22:10.938
- Nobody's rubbing anything.

22:10.981 --> 22:12.374
Call me later.

22:12.418 --> 22:15.334
[scrubbing]

22:17.640 --> 22:20.904
- I'm gonna lose
my security deposit, aren't I?

22:20.948 --> 22:23.472
♪

22:23.516 --> 22:26.170
- Say...

22:26.214 --> 22:28.782
I was right.

22:28.825 --> 22:30.479
Robbie Deck?

22:30.523 --> 22:32.786
Pfffttt.
[laughs]

22:32.829 --> 22:34.396
- Can't you be serious?

22:34.440 --> 22:36.833
- Oh, come on.
This is serious.

22:36.877 --> 22:39.140
The hell else do you think
I moved back here

22:39.183 --> 22:42.926
if not to rub everybody's noses
in how freaking cool I am?

22:42.970 --> 22:45.059
♪

22:45.102 --> 22:47.409
- Here.

22:47.453 --> 22:49.803
Put this in.

22:49.846 --> 22:52.501
We'll have a line to each other
and one to Raytek outside.

22:52.545 --> 22:53.894
- Copy that, Kemosabe.

22:53.937 --> 22:55.939
Brattle will be
in the science room at 10:00.

22:55.983 --> 22:58.028
- I'll cover
the front entrance.

22:58.072 --> 23:01.118
Raytek and her man
will neutralize Harley and Sid.

23:01.162 --> 23:03.077
When you say the word,

23:03.120 --> 23:05.688
I'll have her take the room.

23:05.732 --> 23:08.038
It's not a great plan.

23:09.997 --> 23:12.956
- Well, it don't have to be.
It just has to work.

23:13.000 --> 23:16.917
[chatter, laughter]

23:16.960 --> 23:19.572
Well, we got a couple hours,
so...

23:19.615 --> 23:22.618
[clears throat]

23:22.662 --> 23:24.794
Probably don't wanna dance,
though, do you?

23:28.015 --> 23:30.931
[tense music]

23:30.974 --> 23:35.022
♪

23:35.065 --> 23:38.634
- I don't like it.

23:38.678 --> 23:39.766
I said I don't like it.

23:39.809 --> 23:43.726
- What don't you like,
Sidney?

23:43.770 --> 23:46.642
- It's been seven years
since Spivey crossed you

23:46.686 --> 23:48.644
and here we are
running back to him

23:48.688 --> 23:51.865
like he's a baby
in a burning building.

23:51.908 --> 23:53.736
- Don't dabble in metaphor,
Sidney.

23:53.780 --> 23:55.085
It's not your strong suit.

23:55.129 --> 23:57.871
- It's just--I thought he had
your mark on him.

23:59.960 --> 24:02.092
Not the other way around.

24:02.136 --> 24:05.052
♪

24:05.095 --> 24:07.446
Boss.

24:09.273 --> 24:10.971
Boss.

24:11.014 --> 24:12.581
- Enough, Sidney.

24:12.625 --> 24:15.584
Signal the boy,
if you must.

24:15.628 --> 24:17.978
♪

24:22.330 --> 24:23.940
- We're out of soda.

24:27.248 --> 24:29.511
How is anyone supposed
to function without caffeine?

24:29.555 --> 24:30.991
- Yeah, sorry, Captain.

24:31.034 --> 24:33.863
The grocery runs have become
grocery walks around here,

24:33.907 --> 24:37.214
what with the explosions
and such.

24:37.258 --> 24:38.825
You can always go down
to the supply closet.

24:42.698 --> 24:45.614
[funky music]

24:45.658 --> 24:52.621
♪

24:53.666 --> 24:56.582
[phone buzzing]

24:57.974 --> 25:00.760
[phone whooshing]

25:00.803 --> 25:03.937
- Oh, shit.

25:03.980 --> 25:06.896
Hey.
Hey!

25:06.940 --> 25:08.289
Mock.
- [whistling casually]

25:08.332 --> 25:09.856
- Open the door.
Come on.

25:09.899 --> 25:12.162
Mock, this isn't funny.

25:14.077 --> 25:17.559
Yeah?

25:17.603 --> 25:20.867
God damn it, Mock!

25:20.910 --> 25:25.132
[rats scampering, squeaking]

25:25.175 --> 25:28.135
[pop ballad]

25:28.178 --> 25:33.836
♪

25:33.880 --> 25:37.274
- I tell you,
I'm not one for regrets,

25:37.318 --> 25:41.017
but, uh...

25:41.061 --> 25:44.020
I feel one coming on.

25:44.064 --> 25:46.936
Well, just that I spent
all those years

25:46.980 --> 25:52.202
inches from the coolest,
meanest,

25:52.246 --> 25:56.772
most interesting person
I'd ever met

25:56.816 --> 25:59.862
and I never once
tried to kiss her.

26:01.429 --> 26:03.953
- I'd have
ripped your head off.

26:03.997 --> 26:06.042
- Mmm.

26:06.086 --> 26:07.391
What a way to go.

26:07.435 --> 26:09.872
[both laugh]

26:09.916 --> 26:12.875
♪

26:15.051 --> 26:16.618
- I got the bleach.

26:20.100 --> 26:22.232
Can you get under
the coffee table?

26:22.276 --> 26:23.277
- Yeah.

26:27.673 --> 26:30.240
Cindy, I'm so sorry

26:30.284 --> 26:33.896
about the loss of your...

26:33.940 --> 26:36.769
what was he, your boyfriend?

26:36.812 --> 26:39.902
- Laigika pariksaka.

26:39.946 --> 26:42.992
Means "sexual explorer"
in San-skirt.

26:44.254 --> 26:45.908
It's a language.

26:45.952 --> 26:47.257
- Right.

26:47.301 --> 26:50.652
I know he provided
all kind of services to people.

26:50.696 --> 26:54.177
Did any of those services
happen to be...

26:54.221 --> 26:56.745
I don't know,

26:56.789 --> 26:58.051
explosive?

26:58.094 --> 27:00.183
- Are you asking
if Harold was a bomber?

27:00.227 --> 27:02.664
- Oh, come on, girl.
No.

27:02.708 --> 27:04.318
Absolutely not.
- Okay.

27:04.361 --> 27:06.712
- I know he was not a bomber.

27:06.755 --> 27:09.105
Maybe he facilitated
for somebody.

27:09.149 --> 27:11.281
Like Ms. Colder perhaps.

27:11.325 --> 27:13.762
- You take that sponge,
and you scrub that thought

27:13.806 --> 27:16.460
right out of your damn mind,
Mr. Singe.

27:16.504 --> 27:19.681
Everybody in this town
wanted something done.

27:19.725 --> 27:22.858
Something
they were ashamed of.

27:22.902 --> 27:25.948
Hal just gave them
what they asked for.

27:27.341 --> 27:31.127
[laughs sobbingly]

27:31.171 --> 27:34.217
Ah.

27:34.261 --> 27:37.699
You know, there have been
three murders here

27:37.743 --> 27:41.224
in one week?
I mean...

27:41.268 --> 27:44.924
this place has got
highly toxic vibes.

27:46.447 --> 27:48.710
I've smudged with sage, like,
half a dozen times,

27:48.754 --> 27:51.844
but my clothes still smell
like tar

27:51.887 --> 27:55.021
from that stupid bomb.

27:55.064 --> 27:56.979
- Tar?

27:57.023 --> 27:58.328
Mm-mm.

27:58.372 --> 28:00.243
I don't remember that bomb
smelling like tar.

28:00.287 --> 28:01.897
- The first one.

28:01.941 --> 28:03.812
The one that killed
the landlady.

28:05.901 --> 28:09.339
Oh.
[sniffles]

28:09.383 --> 28:11.037
This is what I was wearing
when it--

28:11.080 --> 28:13.779
[mimics explosion]
You know?

28:13.822 --> 28:15.171
Smell it.

28:15.215 --> 28:16.999
- [inhales sharply]
- Yeah.

28:17.043 --> 28:19.480
That's tar.

28:19.523 --> 28:21.090
- Shit.

28:21.134 --> 28:23.179
That is tar.

28:23.223 --> 28:27.444
[dramatic music]

28:27.488 --> 28:30.186
- King Tutankhamun was buried

28:30.230 --> 28:31.535
with 300 clay servants...
- What is this?

28:31.579 --> 28:33.059
- Shh!
- Meant to reanimate

28:33.102 --> 28:34.974
in the next world,

28:35.017 --> 28:38.760
not unlike our gig economy
robber barons...

28:38.804 --> 28:40.501
- Come on.
Who listens to this shit?

28:40.544 --> 28:42.459
- I do.
- Workers to toil eternally.

28:42.503 --> 28:44.374
- Turn this crap off.

28:44.418 --> 28:45.811
- You think it's crap?

28:45.854 --> 28:47.856
Show me the lie.
- [scoffs]

28:47.900 --> 28:49.510
- Debate me, coward.

28:49.553 --> 28:50.946
Come on.

28:50.990 --> 28:52.556
- License and registration.

28:52.600 --> 28:54.428
- Shut your mouth
if you wanna keep your teeth.

28:54.471 --> 28:57.126
♪

28:57.170 --> 28:58.867
- They gave me my clothes back
at the hospital.

28:58.911 --> 29:00.347
They didn't smell
anything like tar.

29:00.390 --> 29:01.957
- Yeah, that's odd, right?

29:02.001 --> 29:03.219
- Yeah.

29:03.263 --> 29:04.351
- So how's the reunion going?

29:04.394 --> 29:06.179
- [scoffs]
Don't ask.

29:06.222 --> 29:08.398
Pick me up after?
We should talk through this.

29:08.442 --> 29:10.096
- A'ight.

29:10.139 --> 29:12.141
- Is this damn thing working?

29:12.185 --> 29:13.490
Allegra, you hearing me?

29:13.534 --> 29:15.884
- Yes, I can hear you.

29:15.928 --> 29:17.581
- All targets neutralized
out here.

29:17.625 --> 29:19.496
No sign of El Jefe.

29:19.540 --> 29:21.150
- Then he's on his way to us.

29:21.194 --> 29:23.152
- Oh, I thought about
getting into frackin'.

29:23.196 --> 29:25.981
I mean, I sure as shit
know about shale.

29:26.025 --> 29:27.287
[laughter]

29:27.330 --> 29:29.071
Say, any of y'all own
exotic animals?

29:29.115 --> 29:31.073
- Hey.
Can we talk?

29:31.117 --> 29:32.379
- Yeah, sure thing.

29:32.422 --> 29:33.946
'Scuse me, fellas.

29:35.904 --> 29:39.038
- Why would one bomb
smell different than another?

29:39.081 --> 29:41.605
- It's almost go-time.
What are you doing?

29:41.649 --> 29:44.260
- Do you know of a bomb
that smells like tar?

29:44.304 --> 29:46.088
- C4?
- Okay.

29:46.132 --> 29:49.004
And one that smells
like nothing?

29:49.048 --> 29:51.267
- I mean, Semtex maybe,

29:51.311 --> 29:52.312
but it'd have to be
the old stuff

29:52.355 --> 29:54.880
before they added
a scent to it.

29:54.923 --> 29:56.925
- Why would one person
use two different bombs?

29:56.969 --> 29:58.361
- I don't know.
He wouldn't.

29:58.405 --> 29:59.580
What are you getting at?
- Testin', testin'!

29:59.623 --> 30:02.104
[microphone feedback]
Howdy, y'all.

30:02.148 --> 30:03.932
I said howdy, y'all!

30:03.976 --> 30:05.847
[awkward cough]

30:05.891 --> 30:07.327
- Okay, uh...

30:07.370 --> 30:09.938
Duke?

30:09.982 --> 30:12.071
It's good to see
the class of '99

30:12.114 --> 30:13.463
looking 90-fine.

30:13.507 --> 30:15.465
[White Town's "Your Woman"]

30:15.509 --> 30:17.337
After this slow dance,

30:17.380 --> 30:19.861
we're gonna be serving
whoopie pies

30:19.905 --> 30:21.123
in the weight room.

30:21.167 --> 30:23.430
♪

30:23.473 --> 30:25.171
♪ Just tell me

30:25.214 --> 30:29.958
♪ What you got
to say to me ♪

30:30.002 --> 30:31.481
♪

30:31.525 --> 30:34.484
♪ I've been waiting
for so long ♪

30:34.528 --> 30:39.272
♪ To hear the truth

30:39.315 --> 30:41.927
- All right.
[sighs]

30:41.970 --> 30:45.321
It's Clyde o'clock.
How do I look?

30:45.365 --> 30:47.062
- Stay calm.
Okay?

30:47.106 --> 30:49.978
- Mm-hmm.

30:50.022 --> 30:51.501
- ♪ Tell me
that we're through ♪

30:51.545 --> 30:53.503
- He doesn't own you anymore.

30:53.547 --> 30:55.897
- Yeah.
I know.

30:55.941 --> 30:58.291
I know.

30:58.334 --> 31:00.989
- Hey.
- Hmm.

31:01.033 --> 31:02.425
- I'm right here.

31:02.469 --> 31:04.166
- Mm-hmm.

31:04.210 --> 31:07.474
- ♪ You don't even know

31:07.517 --> 31:12.131
♪ You're being unkind

31:12.174 --> 31:15.482
♪ So much for all
your highbrow ♪

31:15.525 --> 31:19.573
♪ Marxist ways

31:19.616 --> 31:21.531
♪ Just use me up

31:21.575 --> 31:26.406
♪ And then you walk away

31:26.449 --> 31:30.323
♪ Boy, you can't play me
that way ♪

31:30.366 --> 31:36.938
♪

31:36.982 --> 31:38.157
- Go.

31:38.200 --> 31:43.031
♪

31:43.075 --> 31:47.035
- ♪ I could never be
your woman ♪

31:47.079 --> 31:52.040
♪

31:52.084 --> 31:55.391
♪ When I saw my best friend

31:55.435 --> 31:59.743
♪ Yesterday

31:59.787 --> 32:03.269
♪ She said
she never liked you ♪

32:03.312 --> 32:07.577
♪ From the start

32:07.621 --> 32:09.405
♪ Well, me

32:09.449 --> 32:14.106
♪ I wish that I could claim
the same ♪

32:16.108 --> 32:19.502
♪ But you always knew
you held my heart ♪

32:19.546 --> 32:21.156
- Jake, what's your 20?

32:21.200 --> 32:23.071
- I'm approaching
the science room.

32:23.115 --> 32:25.987
All clear so far.
- All right, standing by.

32:26.031 --> 32:28.990
- What the hell?

32:29.034 --> 32:31.645
I'm in the science room.
Brattle's not here.

32:31.688 --> 32:33.429
- His van's on site.
I arrested his men.

32:33.473 --> 32:34.735
Where the hell is he?

32:34.778 --> 32:38.347
[Pulp's "Do You Remember
the First Time?"]

32:38.391 --> 32:41.611
[upbeat synth pop]

32:41.655 --> 32:43.048
- Oh, shit.

32:43.091 --> 32:45.267
He's at the party.

32:45.311 --> 32:47.095
By the punch bowl.

32:47.139 --> 32:52.100
♪

32:52.144 --> 32:56.626
- ♪ You say
you've gotta go home ♪

32:56.670 --> 32:59.629
♪ 'Cause he's sitting
on his own ♪

32:59.673 --> 33:01.631
♪ Again this evening

33:01.675 --> 33:04.025
♪

33:04.069 --> 33:07.376
♪ And I know
you're gonna let him ♪

33:07.420 --> 33:09.465
♪ Bore your pants off again

33:09.509 --> 33:11.032
- Jake.

33:11.076 --> 33:12.468
- ♪ Oh,
now it's half past 8:00 ♪

33:12.512 --> 33:13.817
- Don't let him get to you.

33:13.861 --> 33:16.429
- ♪ You'll be late

33:16.472 --> 33:19.127
♪ Oh, but you say
you're not sure ♪

33:19.171 --> 33:20.694
♪ Ah

33:20.737 --> 33:22.783
♪ Though it makes good sense

33:22.826 --> 33:26.526
♪ For you to live together

33:26.569 --> 33:30.530
- You got old.

33:30.573 --> 33:34.316
- You got fat.

33:34.360 --> 33:37.189
- ♪ And now
it's getting late ♪

33:37.232 --> 33:41.410
♪ He's so straight

33:41.454 --> 33:44.065
♪

33:44.109 --> 33:45.197
♪ Do you remember
the first time? ♪

33:45.240 --> 33:47.503
- Your girlfriend's listening?

33:47.547 --> 33:51.203
- ♪ I can't remember
a worse time ♪

33:51.246 --> 33:53.161
♪ Oh, but you know
that we've changed ♪

33:53.205 --> 33:54.684
♪ So much since then

33:54.728 --> 33:56.686
♪ Oh, yeah, we've grown

33:56.730 --> 33:59.646
- I want you to understand me,
Ms. Dill.

33:59.689 --> 34:02.083
If you try to enter,

34:02.127 --> 34:05.391
everyone in this room

34:05.434 --> 34:07.393
will die.

34:07.436 --> 34:09.482
- ♪ Just as long as you save
a piece for me, oh, yeah ♪

34:09.525 --> 34:13.181
[earpiece beeps]

34:13.225 --> 34:14.182
[punches door]

34:14.226 --> 34:18.839
♪

34:18.882 --> 34:21.885
- Now, let's you and I
have a real talk.

34:21.929 --> 34:24.540
[tense music]

34:24.584 --> 34:27.369
- I'm headed in.

34:27.413 --> 34:29.589
♪

34:29.632 --> 34:31.330
[gunshot]

34:31.373 --> 34:33.375
[sighs]

34:33.419 --> 34:40.295
♪

34:47.781 --> 34:50.740
- Shh.

34:50.784 --> 34:54.701
- Mock didn't deserve that,
Gene.

34:54.744 --> 34:57.269
- I didn't wanna kill him.

34:57.312 --> 34:58.792
Just like I didn't wanna crawl

34:58.835 --> 35:01.490
through a rat shit filled
air conditioning vent,

35:01.534 --> 35:03.536
but he locked me
in a fucking soda closet.

35:03.579 --> 35:06.495
- I know what you are, Gene.
I've known for months now.

35:06.539 --> 35:07.714
- I'm a good cop.

35:07.757 --> 35:10.325
- Please.
[laughs]

35:10.369 --> 35:12.588
You're a contract killer.

35:12.632 --> 35:15.200
And you're not even good
at that.

35:15.243 --> 35:17.158
- This was supposed
to be simple

35:17.202 --> 35:19.856
but you couldn't leave it
alone, you miserable n--

35:19.900 --> 35:22.772
[both grunting]

35:22.816 --> 35:24.861
- [breathing heavily]

35:24.905 --> 35:27.386
Ugh.
Damn it, Gene.

35:27.429 --> 35:30.519
- [grunting]

35:30.563 --> 35:31.955
- [grunts]

35:31.999 --> 35:38.266
♪

35:38.310 --> 35:40.573
- God, I'm gonna
fucking kill you!

35:40.616 --> 35:41.965
- Cut it out!

35:42.009 --> 35:44.577
[both grunting]

35:44.620 --> 35:46.405
[laughs]

35:46.448 --> 35:49.495
[both grunting]

35:49.538 --> 35:52.367
Shit. Shit!

35:52.411 --> 35:53.673
[gunshot]

35:53.716 --> 35:56.284
♪

35:56.328 --> 35:57.677
[sighs]

35:57.720 --> 36:00.201
[phone buzzes]

36:00.245 --> 36:02.203
♪

36:02.247 --> 36:03.683
- Shit.

36:03.726 --> 36:08.992
♪

36:09.036 --> 36:10.646
[pop ballad]

36:10.690 --> 36:12.953
- The suspense, Jacob.

36:12.996 --> 36:15.260
It's killing me.

36:15.303 --> 36:17.784
- I don't trust that senator.

36:17.827 --> 36:20.308
I don't think we should be
negotiating against each other.

36:20.352 --> 36:23.311
We should be trying
to figure this.

36:23.355 --> 36:24.965
You know?
For the both of us.

36:25.008 --> 36:26.967
- That's sweet.

36:27.010 --> 36:28.795
And maybe we can play
a game of catch

36:28.838 --> 36:30.318
in your yard after.

36:30.362 --> 36:34.496
♪

36:34.540 --> 36:37.847
You told him.

36:37.891 --> 36:40.894
About Al-Namur.

36:40.937 --> 36:43.331
I knew you would.

36:43.375 --> 36:45.855
- ♪ Where have you been
all my life? ♪

36:45.899 --> 36:47.944
- Ooh, hello.
Hello.

36:53.515 --> 36:54.951
- How'd he take it?

36:54.995 --> 36:56.779
Badly, I assume.

36:56.823 --> 37:00.696
Your version lacks
a hero narrative,

37:00.740 --> 37:01.871
which should
teach you something

37:01.915 --> 37:03.438
I thought you learned
a long time ago.

37:03.482 --> 37:05.875
[laughs]
You're not the hero.

37:07.790 --> 37:11.490
You have never taken
responsibility

37:11.533 --> 37:13.535
for the terrible things
you did.

37:13.579 --> 37:15.494
- Things you made me do.

37:15.537 --> 37:17.539
- Jake.
[laughs]

37:17.583 --> 37:19.715
What are you doing here

37:19.759 --> 37:21.891
in this pathetic little town?

37:21.935 --> 37:23.893
And you're retired?

37:23.937 --> 37:26.374
Sad.

37:26.418 --> 37:29.072
It makes me sad.

37:29.116 --> 37:36.036
♪

37:37.646 --> 37:41.433
I heard what you did
to my Anatol at your mansion.

37:41.476 --> 37:43.913
Clubbed him into abstraction.

37:43.957 --> 37:48.962
♪

37:49.005 --> 37:52.095
That's because you are
a beautiful weapon, Jacob.

37:52.139 --> 37:54.620
[sinister music]

37:54.663 --> 37:56.709
A fist.

37:56.752 --> 37:58.667
- Stop it.

37:58.711 --> 38:00.756
- I've had someone planted
in this town

38:00.800 --> 38:02.149
for more than a year

38:02.192 --> 38:05.805
and he hasn't been able
to lay a finger on you.

38:05.848 --> 38:09.939
None of my boys make up
even one half

38:09.983 --> 38:12.420
of Jacob Spivey.

38:12.464 --> 38:14.335
- Raytek.

38:14.379 --> 38:15.815
Brattle has an inside man.

38:15.858 --> 38:18.731
[silence]

38:18.774 --> 38:19.993
What's going on?

38:20.036 --> 38:21.995
[feedback whine]

38:22.038 --> 38:25.085
Shit.

38:25.128 --> 38:26.869
All right, I'm coming to you.

38:30.786 --> 38:32.440
- Well, look, Clyde,
if you're gonna kill me,

38:32.484 --> 38:33.963
just go on
and get it over with.

38:34.007 --> 38:36.009
'Cause at least then,

38:36.052 --> 38:38.359
I won't have to listen
to your jabber anymore.

38:38.403 --> 38:42.537
- Kill you?
[laughs]

38:42.581 --> 38:45.453
I'm here to destroy you.

38:45.497 --> 38:46.976
You crossed me, Jacob.

38:47.020 --> 38:49.370
So I've taken your money,
I've taken your men,

38:49.414 --> 38:50.980
and I have rid you
of the notion

38:51.024 --> 38:53.766
that you, Jacob Spivey,

38:53.809 --> 38:56.159
could ever be a good person.

38:56.203 --> 39:00.947
♪

39:00.990 --> 39:02.905
So now, all that's left...

39:02.949 --> 39:05.821
♪

39:05.865 --> 39:08.650
Is for you to come with me.

39:10.609 --> 39:12.698
- Well, that's mighty kind
of you, Clyde.

39:14.569 --> 39:18.704
But all things being equal,

39:18.747 --> 39:20.706
I think I'd rather go
to prison.

39:20.749 --> 39:24.449
- Oh, Jake.

39:24.492 --> 39:26.842
Things were never equal.

39:26.886 --> 39:32.674
♪

39:32.718 --> 39:34.459
[explosion]

39:34.502 --> 39:37.113
[screaming]

39:37.157 --> 39:43.729
♪

39:58.657 --> 40:01.703
[screaming and shouting]

40:01.747 --> 40:08.754
♪

40:08.797 --> 40:11.496
[dogs barking distantly]

40:16.109 --> 40:19.242
- Colder.

40:19.286 --> 40:21.157
- Allegra.
Wow, are you okay?

40:21.201 --> 40:22.115
Do you need help?

40:22.158 --> 40:23.725
- Where's Raytek?

40:23.769 --> 40:25.031
- I don't know.

40:25.074 --> 40:29.209
[distant sirens wailing]

40:29.252 --> 40:31.211
- Did you just get here?

40:31.254 --> 40:34.083
- I heard the explosion.

40:34.127 --> 40:35.607
Crowd trampled right into me
like cattle.

40:35.650 --> 40:39.088
I think they broke my nose.

40:39.132 --> 40:42.831
- You're always where
the action is, aren't you?

40:42.875 --> 40:45.530
- I'm police, Allegra.
It's my job.

40:47.183 --> 40:49.098
- You smell like tar.

40:49.142 --> 40:52.711
♪

40:52.754 --> 40:55.235
That explosion.

40:55.278 --> 40:56.758
That was you, wasn't it?

40:56.802 --> 40:57.803
- What are you saying?

40:57.846 --> 41:00.283
- You work for Clyde Brattle.

41:00.327 --> 41:02.285
You're the inside man.

41:02.329 --> 41:04.244
- [laughs]
Come on.

41:04.287 --> 41:08.161
- Felicity didn't love you.

41:08.204 --> 41:09.989
She was investigating you.

41:10.032 --> 41:13.035
You found out

41:13.079 --> 41:14.602
and you blew her up.

41:14.646 --> 41:16.648
- Please.
You know I have an alibi.

41:16.691 --> 41:18.214
- For the second bomb.

41:18.258 --> 41:19.825
For Strucker.

41:19.868 --> 41:23.742
But you didn't blow up
Strucker.

41:23.785 --> 41:25.700
It was a second bomber.

41:25.744 --> 41:28.137
- You don't know
what you're talking about.

41:28.181 --> 41:30.662
- Felicity's boyfriend
did kill her.

41:33.795 --> 41:35.275
And it was you.

41:40.585 --> 41:44.153
- [grunts]

41:44.197 --> 41:45.981
- [yelps]

41:46.025 --> 41:48.244
[both grunting]

41:48.288 --> 41:51.073
[Captain Beefheart & His Magic
Band's "Too Much Time"]

41:51.117 --> 41:55.861
♪

41:55.904 --> 42:00.996
- ♪ I got too much time

42:01.040 --> 42:03.651
♪ Too much time

42:03.695 --> 42:04.739
- Shit.

42:04.783 --> 42:07.002
- ♪ I got too much time

42:07.046 --> 42:09.875
♪ To be without love

42:09.918 --> 42:13.574
♪ Too much time

42:13.618 --> 42:17.752
♪ I got too much time

42:17.796 --> 42:20.102
♪ I got
too much time ♪

42:20.146 --> 42:22.975
♪

42:23.018 --> 42:27.849
♪ Too much time
to be without love ♪

42:27.893 --> 42:31.940
♪ In my life,
I've got a deep devotion ♪

42:31.984 --> 42:36.249
♪ Wide as the sky
and deep as the ocean ♪

42:36.292 --> 42:40.601
♪ Every war that's waged
makes me cry ♪

42:40.645 --> 42:44.997
♪ Every bird that goes by
